scholar in Spanish

00:00:21.020 --> 00:00:23.200
sociolinguistics, and has
studied in Ecuador, Ireland,

00:00:23.200 --> 00:00:24.750
and the United States.

00:00:24.750 --> 00:00:27.440
She is author of "Telephone
Interpreting," the first book

00:00:27.440 --> 00:00:31.380
ever written on the topic, and
"Found in Translation: How

00:00:31.380 --> 00:00:35.390
Language Shapes Our Lives and
Transforms the World." So

00:00:35.390 --> 00:00:38.840
again, if you could hold your
questions till the end, we'll

00:00:38.840 --> 00:00:42.050
have Nataly up here to speak.

