00:45:09.100 --> 00:45:13.420
My question is about the term
"translator." When you talk

00:45:13.420 --> 00:45:17.480
about translator, can you give
us some thoughts on community?

00:45:17.480 --> 00:45:19.030
Is it an individual person?

00:45:19.030 --> 00:45:20.410
Is it a community?

00:45:20.410 --> 00:45:24.200
And what do these generative
creative types--

00:45:24.200 --> 00:45:25.240
what's the profile?

00:45:25.240 --> 00:45:26.930
NATALY KELLY: Mm-hmm.

00:45:26.930 --> 00:45:28.970
Well, this is a complicated
question.

00:45:28.970 --> 00:45:32.090
I just wrote an article on this
exact topic, about how

00:45:32.090 --> 00:45:36.250
translators are defining
themselves, and the reality

00:45:36.250 --> 00:45:39.290
is, even the lay public will
call an interpreter a

00:45:39.290 --> 00:45:40.430
translator.

00:45:40.430 --> 00:45:43.640
And even someone who works in
transcreation is usually

00:45:43.640 --> 00:45:45.520
referred to as a translator,
even if what they're doing

00:45:45.520 --> 00:45:47.800
really isn't translation.

00:45:47.800 --> 00:45:50.330
So, the word translation--

00:45:50.330 --> 00:45:53.190
I've used this term in this
presentation, because I have

00:45:53.190 --> 00:45:56.290
been using the overarching term
related to transferring

00:45:56.290 --> 00:45:58.280
information from one language
into another.

00:45:58.280 --> 00:46:00.220
And that's the basic definition
that you'll find in

00:46:00.220 --> 00:46:02.170
most dictionaries.

00:46:02.170 --> 00:46:04.250
What we're finding is-- in some
of the studies that we're

00:46:04.250 --> 00:46:05.880
doing at Common Sense
Advisory--

00:46:05.880 --> 00:46:09.260
is that this word, and what
it means, is changing

00:46:09.260 --> 00:46:10.510
drastically.

00:46:10.510 --> 00:46:12.980
So we just a recent
study on pricing.

00:46:12.980 --> 00:46:15.490
And the big finding was that
the price of translation--

00:46:15.490 --> 00:46:17.890
average price of translation
has dropped.

00:46:17.890 --> 00:46:19.460
Nobody likes to hear that.

00:46:19.460 --> 00:46:20.890
Don't shoot the messenger.

00:46:20.890 --> 00:46:22.770
Well, maybe some people do like
it, if you're buying a

00:46:22.770 --> 00:46:23.250
translation.

00:46:23.250 --> 00:46:25.690
But nobody on the supply side
likes to hear that.

00:46:25.690 --> 00:46:29.830
But what we found is that the
reason for that is that this

00:46:29.830 --> 00:46:31.810
field is becoming
more diverse.

00:46:31.810 --> 00:46:32.530
So now--

00:46:32.530 --> 00:46:35.200
it used to be many years ago,
if you bought translation by

00:46:35.200 --> 00:46:37.380
the word, you would get
translation, editing and

00:46:37.380 --> 00:46:38.620
proofing including
in the price per

00:46:38.620 --> 00:46:40.690
word, included in that.

00:46:40.690 --> 00:46:43.400
Now if you buy translation,
you're only getting

00:46:43.400 --> 00:46:46.530
translation from a lot of
vendors, and you're separately

00:46:46.530 --> 00:46:48.360
paying for editing, and you're
separately paying for

00:46:48.360 --> 00:46:49.740
proofing, and you're separately
paying for

00:46:49.740 --> 00:46:51.370
translation memory management.

00:46:51.370 --> 00:46:54.000
And you're separately paying for
hosting your translation

00:46:54.000 --> 00:46:56.550
memory files in perpetuity.

00:46:56.550 --> 00:46:59.190
You're separately paying for
terminology management.

00:46:59.190 --> 00:47:01.590
You're separately paying
for project management.

00:47:01.590 --> 00:47:03.990
Many of these things are
being broken up now.

00:47:03.990 --> 00:47:07.060
So the field is getting more
diverse in many senses.

00:47:07.060 --> 00:47:10.630
And buyers are starting to
pay separately for that.

00:47:10.630 --> 00:47:12.290
So it's not necessarily
that the price

00:47:12.290 --> 00:47:14.380
is dropping on average.

00:47:14.380 --> 00:47:17.420
It's that many more things
are being built in--

00:47:17.420 --> 00:47:19.490
were-- used to be built into
that price per word that

00:47:19.490 --> 00:47:22.480
aren't any more.

00:47:22.480 --> 00:47:26.310
So there's a lot that goes into
that word translation.

00:47:26.310 --> 00:47:27.640
And we're tracking that.

00:47:27.640 --> 00:47:30.210
And we actually are doing a
study on production models, to

00:47:30.210 --> 00:47:33.430
see how different language
service providers are managing

00:47:33.430 --> 00:47:34.080
that process.

00:47:34.080 --> 00:47:35.650
And now, we're starting
to see more

00:47:35.650 --> 00:47:37.830
collaborative forms emerge.

00:47:37.830 --> 00:47:40.630
I talked to a language service
provider the other day, and

00:47:40.630 --> 00:47:43.250
they told me that they don't
have a TEP process-- a

00:47:43.250 --> 00:47:45.070
Translate, Edit,
Proof process.

00:47:45.070 --> 00:47:46.480
What they're doing
is they have two

00:47:46.480 --> 00:47:48.260
translators who work together.

00:47:48.260 --> 00:47:49.060
Neither--

00:47:49.060 --> 00:47:50.150
there's no hierarchy.

00:47:50.150 --> 00:47:52.940
They're a pair, kind of like
pair programming, and they are

00:47:52.940 --> 00:47:54.520
pair translating.

00:47:54.520 --> 00:47:56.250
They are truly pair translating,
and working as a

00:47:56.250 --> 00:47:58.110
team, and translating
together.

00:47:58.110 --> 00:48:00.400
And so they both have to be
comfortable with the output.

00:48:00.400 --> 00:48:02.380
They both have to be comfortable
with the quality.

00:48:02.380 --> 00:48:05.490
But it saves them the quality
assurance steps, because

00:48:05.490 --> 00:48:07.200
they're doing it from the start
and they're doing it

00:48:07.200 --> 00:48:09.330
together, and they're allowing
collaboration.

00:48:09.330 --> 00:48:11.430
And all of you are probably
familiar with crowdsource

00:48:11.430 --> 00:48:12.860
translation, community
translation.

00:48:12.860 --> 00:48:14.510
We've written a ton
about that.

00:48:14.510 --> 00:48:17.230
That's another form that's less
common, but is still a

00:48:17.230 --> 00:48:20.225
form that is changing the
way we view translation.

00:48:24.198 --> 00:48:25.570
Yes.

00:48:25.570 --> 00:48:26.410
MIKE: My--

00:48:26.410 --> 00:48:27.340
sorry.

00:48:27.340 --> 00:48:28.020
My name's Mike.

00:48:28.020 --> 00:48:30.610
Thank you for your time, and
it was a very interesting

00:48:30.610 --> 00:48:32.070
presentation.

